</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,1474,1576]" pageId="2" pageNumber="38">
The specific epithet ʻ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Júnior &amp; Ázara &amp; Ferreira" authorityYear="2021" box="[440,548,1474,1500]" class="Arachnida" family="Gonyleptidae" genus="Eusarcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Opiliones" pageId="2" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capixaba">
<emphasis box="[440,548,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="38">capixaba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ʼ is derived from the TUpi langUage, meaning ʻfield landʼ, in allUsion to corn and mandioca fields cUltivated by local Indian tribes. It also refers to the natives of the Brazilian state of 
<collectingRegion box="[282,453,1549,1575]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="2" pageNumber="38">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
